## CRUD + API-Level Coverage (PRIMARY DIRECTIVE)

For every module explored, full CRUD operations are a **primary directive** — not optional. Every workflow replay must include all CRUD paths and capture the corresponding network requests:

| Operation | What to replay | Network check |
|-----------|---------------|---------------|
| **Create** | Complete the create form/wizard end-to-end | `playwright-cli request <n>` — verify `POST`/`PUT` URL, status code (201/200), request body schema |
| **Read** | Load list view + detail page | Verify `GET` requests return the expected shape; flag 4xx/5xx or empty payloads |
| **Update** | Edit a resource (inline edit, modal, YAML editor) | Verify `PATCH`/`PUT` endpoint, changed fields, response code (200/202) |
| **Delete** | Delete a resource (single + bulk where available) | Verify `DELETE` endpoint pattern, confirm 200/202/204; check resource disappears from list |

#### Capturing network traffic inline with workflow replay

After each CRUD action, immediately inspect network traffic before moving on:
```bash
playwright-cli requests            # list all requests since page load
playwright-cli request <n>         # inspect the relevant request — headers, body, response
playwright-cli console error       # catch any JS errors triggered by the operation
```

Document each CRUD endpoint in the issue or Interaction Plan entry:
```
CRUD Endpoint (Create): POST /apis/kubevirt.io/v1/namespaces/{ns}/virtualmachines → 201
CRUD Endpoint (Delete): DELETE /apis/kubevirt.io/v1/namespaces/{ns}/virtualmachines/{name} → 200
```

Any CRUD path where the network request returns an unexpected status code, empty payload, or the UI does not reflect the API response is itself a **bug finding** and must be documented as a Phase 3 issue with the full network evidence.

API gaps: if a CRUD operation has UI test coverage but no matching test in `playwright/tests/api/`, note it in the Recommendations section as a candidate for `/api-cross-check`.

