## Rules

- **Read-only** — this agent does NOT modify code, create branches, or commit
- **Match Playwright viewport** — resize to 1920×1080 at the start of the session (`playwright-cli resize 1920 1080`). This ensures screenshots and element visibility match actual test conditions.
- **Load auth state first** — run `playwright-cli state-load playwright/mcp-validations/.auth/openshift-state.json` before navigating. Do not log in manually unless the saved state is missing or expired.
- **Start tracing immediately** — run `playwright-cli tracing-start` right after session setup. This captures the full session evidence without needing to reproduce issues separately.
- **Virtualization view** — always verify the sidebar shows "Virtualization" before interacting
- **Evidence-first** — every issue must have at least a screenshot + snapshot as evidence; use `video-start`/`video-stop` for complex reproduction sequences
- **Don't fix** — report issues, don't try to fix the application or the tests
- **Distinguish test bugs from app bugs** — if a test assertion is wrong, that's not an app bug
- **Be thorough but targeted** — replay workflows from actual test cases, don't randomly click
- **Console/network check** — always check for JS errors (`playwright-cli console error`) and failed API calls (`playwright-cli network`) at each step
- **Resource creation via MCP** — if a workflow requires a resource (VM, namespace), follow the resource creation policy from `cnv-exploration.mdc` (prefer `k8sClient` methods in test code, document any ad-hoc `oc` usage during exploration)
- **Cluster state awareness** — call `get_cluster_info` to capture cluster/CNV version for the report; some issues may be version-specific. **Fallback**: note versions from the console UI footer
- **Artifact cleanup** — after the bug hunt report is produced, delete ALL intermediate artifacts from the session. This includes screenshots (`*.png`), log dumps (`*.log`), DOM snapshots (`*.yml`, `*.html`, `*.txt`), files in `.playwright-mcp/` and `.playwright-cli/`, and any video files not included in the report. Use `rm -f` to clean up. The final report text and any evidence files explicitly referenced in the report are the deliverables — everything else must be removed.
